snippet.textDisplay:
When any ordinary Punjabi would listen this song, he must remember how organically mixed the punjabi population was before the partition. These two guys of Punjab present all three major communities which Punjab had back then. They refer to Sachche Badshah for Sikhs, Allah for Muslims and Bhole (Shiv) for Hindus and call themselves devotee of all three. 

The creation of Pakistan tore apart the most compound pluralistic society and culture of India at that time. Though Pakistan was not demanded by Punjabi Muslims but after partition, Punjab of Pakistani side suddenly turned into a complete hell for Sikhs and Hindus and today, it has 99.8% Muslims. I want to highlight the element of tragedy here more than blaming anyone.
